Dscription:
The objective of this project is to improve the socio-economic well-being and resilience of farming households by promoting climate-smart agriculture (CSA) practices and agricultural entrepreneurship in the Tambacounda and Sédhiou regions in Senegal. AVENIR is funded by GAC (Global Affairs Canada) and implemented by MEDA (Mennonite Economic Development Associates) in collaboration with The Alliance.
AVENIR aims to achieve:
- socio-economic empowerment of women and youth through enhanced leadership capacity on adaptation to climate change, increased capacity to operate agribusiness and improved access to market;
- improved local governance and territorial management of water resources through increased capacity of local/territorial actors to manage water resources and increased capacity of farmers;
- intensification of irrigated and climates change adopted crops through increased access to inputs, technologies and techniques and increased capacity of inputs providers.

